parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intrusion of coolant into the engine cylinders can cause engine damage, overheating, and potentially lead to a fire, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: White smoke coming from the exhaust pipe
loud knocking noise from the engine
and the check engine warning light illuminating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the flex plate or flywheel can cause the engine to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Abnormal rattling sound from the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch or transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: and clutch pedal feeling soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, increasing the risk of a crash, or a vehicle fire in the trunk area, which can result in injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle may not start or may display a "Stop Safely Now" message while driving
followed by a loss of power within a few seconds. The battery energy control module (BECM) may become damaged due to excess voltage and current flow
resulting in a loss of motive power or a vehicle fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hybrid battery can cause the vehicle to lose power and result in a loss of motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The hybrid battery may stop working
and the vehicle may not be able to recharge. The battery may also be damaged due to excess voltage and current flow
resulting in a loss of motive power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-knock sensor can cause the engine to malfunction, resulting in a loss of power and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The check engine light may illuminate
and the vehicle may experience rough starts and loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the gear shift bushing can cause the vehicle to lose power and result in a loss of motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The vehicle may not be able to shift into gear
and the gear shift bushing may deteriorate and break off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the APIM (Audio and Primary Input Module) can cause the instrument panel and infotainment system to malfunction, resulting in a distraction to the driver and increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: The rear-view camera may activate while in drive
and the instrument panel and infotainment system may act erratically

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the flex plate can cause the transmission to malfunction, leading to loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or hesitate, potentially leading to accidents.
Engine overheating can cause engine damage, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents.
The failure of the shift system can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to loss of power, stalling, and potentially causing accidents.
The failure of the lane keep assist system can cause the vehicle to drift out of its lane, potentially leading to accidents.
The failure of the 3G modem can cause the vehicle's remote connection and app features to malfunction.
symptoms: inability to use remote connection and app features.
